org.javaavc.ffmpeg.avfilter

Class AVFilterLink

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sun.jna.Structure
      • org.javaavc.ffmpeg.avfilter.AVFilterLink
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AVFilterLink.ByReference, AVFilterLink.ByValue

    public class AVFilterLink
extends com.sun.jna.Structure
    A link between two filters. This contains pointers to the source and
    destination filters between which this link exists, and the indexes of
    the pads involved. In addition, this link also contains the parameters
    which have been negotiated and agreed upon between the filter, such as
    image dimensions, format, etc.
    This file was autogenerated by JNAerator,
    a tool written by Olivier Chafik that uses a few opensource projects..
    For help, please visit NativeLibs4Java , Rococoa, or JNA.

      • time_base

        public AVRational time_base
        Define the time base used by the PTS of the frames/samples
        which will pass through this link.
        During the configuration stage, each filter is supposed to
        change only the output timebase, while the timebase of the
        input link is assumed to be an unchangeable property.
        C type : AVRational

      • in_formats

        public com.sun.jna.ptr.PointerByReference in_formats
        Lists of formats and channel layouts supported by the input and output
        filters respectively. These lists are used for negotiating the format
        to actually be used, which will be loaded into the format and
        channel_layout members, above, when chosen.
        C type : AVFilterFormats*

      • request_samples

        public int request_samples
        Audio only, the destination filter sets this to a non-zero value to
        request that buffers with the given number of samples should be sent to
        it. AVFilterPad.needs_fifo must also be set on the corresponding input
        pad.
        Last buffer before EOF will be padded with silence.

      • frame_rate

        public AVRational frame_rate
        Frame rate of the stream on the link, or 1/0 if unknown;
        if left to 0/0, will be automatically be copied from the first input
        of the source filter if it exists.
        * Sources should set it to the best estimation of the real frame rate.
        Filters should update it if necessary depending on their function.
        Sinks can use it to set a default output frame rate.
        It is similar to the r_frame_rate field in AVStream.
        C type : AVRational

      • partial_buf

        public AVFrame.ByReference partial_buf
        Buffer partially filled with samples to achieve a fixed/minimum size.
        C type : AVFrame*

      • partial_buf_size

        public int partial_buf_size
        Size of the partial buffer to allocate.
        Must be between min_samples and max_samples.

      • min_samples

        public int min_samples
        Minimum number of samples to filter at once. If filter_frame() is
        called with fewer samples, it will accumulate them in partial_buf.
        This field and the related ones must not be changed after filtering
        has started.
        If 0, all related fields are ignored.

      • max_samples

        public int max_samples
        Maximum number of samples to filter at once. If filter_frame() is
        called with more samples, it will split them.

      • cur_buf_copy

        public AVFilterBufferRef.ByReference cur_buf_copy
        The buffer reference currently being received across the link by the
        destination filter. This is used internally by the filter system to
        allow automatic copying of buffers which do not have sufficient
        permissions for the destination. This should not be accessed directly
        by the filters.
        C type : AVFilterBufferRef*

      • closed

        public int closed
        True if the link is closed.
        If set, all attemps of start_frame, filter_frame or request_frame
        will fail with AVERROR_EOF, and if necessary the reference will be
        destroyed.
        If request_frame returns AVERROR_EOF, this flag is set on the
        corresponding link.
        It can be set also be set by either the source or the destination
        filter.
